items.title: Gemini 3 and Nano Banana Pro in Search are coming to more countries around the world.
items.summary: We're bringing our most intelligent model yet, Gemini 3 Pro, to Google Search in more countries around the world . The Gemini Pro is the latest model of the Gemini Pro to be added to the Google Search service . We are happy to announce that Gemini Pro will be available in the U.S. for the first time in the next few months .

items.title: Ideas: Community building, machine learning, and the future of AI
items.summary: The Women in Machine Learning Workshop (WiML) marks its 20th annual gathering . Cofounders, friends, and collaborators Jenn Wortman Vaughan and Hanna Wallach reflect on WiML’s evolution, navigating the field of ML, and their work in responsible AI . The post: Ideas: Community building, machine learning, and the future of AI .

items.title: MIT offshoot Liquid AI releases blueprint for enterprise-grade small-model training
items.summary: Liquid AI is publishing a detailed blueprint that other organizations can use as a reference for training their own small, efficient models from scratch . LFM2 is built around a repeatable recipe: a hardware-in-the-loop search process, a training curriculum that compensates for smaller parameter budgets, and a post-training pipeline tuned for instruction following and tool use .

items.title: OpenAGI emerges from stealth with an AI agent that it claims crushes OpenAI and Anthropic
items.summary: San Francisco-based startup claims its new AI model can control computers better than systems built by OpenAI and Anthropic . Lux is a foundation model designed to operate computers autonomously by interpreting screenshots and executing actions across desktop applications . Lux achieves an 83.6 percent success rate on a benchmark that has become the industry's most rigorous test for evaluating AI agents that control computers .

items.title: Capture the full value of your technology with financial intelligence
items.summary: As AI, cloud, and other technology investments soar, organizations have to make investment decisions with increased speed and clarity . Real control over technology spend comes from financial intelligence — turning fragmented inputs into actionable, context-rich insights . By connecting financial, operational, and business data across the enterprise, they give leaders the clarity to make every tech dollar count .

items.title: Agent coordination is the missing piece in AI commerce — new AWS and Visa blueprints target the gap
items.summary: Amazon is listing Visa’s Intelligence Commerce platform on the AWS Marketplace . Amazon says it's making it easier for enterprises to connect to tools that enable agentic payments . Visa and AWS are helping to provide the foundational infrastructure for developers and businesses to pursue agentic commerce projects . For this to work, developers must coordinate several agents and understand the different needs .

items.title: Transformers v5: Simple model definitions powering the AI ecosystem
items.summary: Transformers v5: Simple model definitions powering the AI ecosystem . The latest Transformers video was released on Wednesday . The Transformers version of Transformers will be released later this month . The new Transformers video will be the first of its kind in the world of AI-powered robots and AI-controlled robots . The company has been working on a new AI-driven platform called AI-enabled Transformers .

items.title: Hybrid cloud security must be rebuilt for an AI war it was never designed to fight
items.summary: More than half (55%) of organizations suffered cloud breaches in the past year . Nearly half of the enterprises polled said their security tools missed the attack entirely . The security architectures designed for the pre-AI era can't keep pace . The industry is finally beginning to respond. CrowdStrike is rolling out a platform designed to compress 15-minute response windows down to seconds .

items.title: Ontology is the real guardrail: How to stop AI agents from misunderstanding your business
items.summary: AI agents are seeing limited success in real-world applications, often due to the inability of agents to truly understand the “meaning” of data in the context of a given business . Enterprise data is mostly siloed into disparate systems in structured and unstructured forms and needs to be analyzed with a domain-specific business lens . For agents to combine data from multiple systems, they must understand different representations .
